<li id="cite_note-37"><b><a href="#cite_ref-37" title="">^</a></b> Thomas, <i>Townshend Duties</i>, 245.</li>
<li id="cite_note-38"><b><a href="#cite_ref-38" title="">^</a></b> Labaree, <i>Tea Party</i>, 102; see also John W. Tyler, <i>Smugglers &amp; Patriots: Boston Merchants and the Advent of the American Revolution</i> (Boston, 1986).</li>
<li id="cite_note-39"><b><a href="#cite_ref-39" title="">^</a></b> Thomas, <i>Townshend Duties</i>, 256.</li>
<li id="cite_note-40"><b><a href="#cite_ref-40" title="">^</a></b> Knollenberg, <i>Growth</i>, 95–96.</li>
<li id="cite_note-41"><b><a href="#cite_ref-41" title="">^</a></b> Knollenberg, <i>Growth</i>, 101.</li>
<li id="cite_note-42"><b><a href="#cite_ref-42" title="">^</a></b> Labaree, <i>Tea Party</i>, 100. See also Alyn Brodsky, <i>Benjamin Rush</i> (Macmillan, 2004), 109.</li>
